Kim Jong Il Inspects Drill Ground of KPA Unit 132 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 3 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected the drill ground of KPA Unit 132.
 He looked round training apparatuses and facilities of the unit before watching the tactical training of commanding officers in the military lecture room. He was pleased to learn that the commanding officers of the unit have been trained as able officers who have acquired high operation commanding capability to successfully carry out the WPK's Juche-oriented military strategy by putting the training on a scientific and regular basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He mounted an observation platform to watch soldiers' training.
 He expressed great satisfaction over the fact that all the commanding officers and soldiers have been fully prepared as a-match-for-a hundred fighters. He highly appreciated the success made by them in training and set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines in bolstering the People's Army as invincible revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our commanding officers and soldiers have built up Herculean strength to win one victory after another, he said, adding that no force on earth can match the KPA.
 Noting that the servicepersons of the unit have very strong enthusiasm for training, he underscored the need for the unit to pay primary attention to the combat and political training at all times, bearing deep in mind that the basic way of building up the matchless strength of the army, the master key to training soldiers as a-match-for-a hundred fighters is to intensify the above-said training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the soldiers' living, going round an education room, field quarters, mess hall, service facilities, a barn and various other places of the drill ground.
 He highly appreciated the efforts made by the unit, saying it is very good that it has successfully built the drill ground for satisfactorily ensuring various forms of training and entertainment, educational and supply service facilities, in particular, so that the soldiers in field training may not feel any slightest inconvenience in living.
 The servicepersons of the KPA are leading a well-regulated life by keeping their camping site neat and tidy even though they spend a single night, he said, adding that this clearly shows the strong discipline and inexhaustible mental power of the KPA, heir to the glorious traditions of the Anti-Japanese Guerrilla Army.
 He gave servicepersons of the unit a pair of binoculars, a machinegun and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and Vice Department Director of the WPK Central Committee Hwang Pyong So.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Staunch Struggle against Imperialism 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 3 (KCNA) -- To give up an anti-imperialist struggle means overlooking and tolerating the imperialists' moves for aggression and war, domination and subjugation and, furthermore, betraying the popular masses' cause of independence, It is necessary to steadily wage the anti-imperialist struggle as long as there remain the imperialists and their moves for domination persist.  Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People should never be deceived by the imperialists' offensive for "peace" and "human rights" but maintain a high degree of vigilance against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' loud-mouthed "peace" and "human rights" are bound to be accompanied by military intervention and war. This is a serious lesson taught by history. 
 The global peace and genuine human rights can be guaranteed only when a firm anti-imperialist independent stand is held fast to. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to see through the reactionary nature and danger of the imperialists' moves for "globalization". Their loudmouthed "globalization" is nothing but a figleaf for covering up their strategy for dominating a unipolar world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to settle problems by preserving the Juche character and the national character in the revolution and construction and building up one's own strength and strengthening the unity and cooperation among the progressive countries.
 No country should yield to the high-handed practices and military pressure of the imperialists. Imperialism is by no means strong. It is dregs of history as it is fated to go to ruin. All countries should have staunch anti-imperialist spirit and build military muscle if they are to emerge victorious in the stand-off with the imperialists.
 It is an important requirement for winning victory in the anti-imperialist struggle and pushing forward the human cause of independence to achieve the unity of the anti-imperialist independent forces. It is necessary to counter the imperialists' tactics of destroying these forces one by one with the strategy of unity. The imperialists are most afraid of the unity of the anti-imperialist independent forces. They should jointly deal blows at the imperialists in the international arena.

Rodong Sinmun on Anti-U.S., Anti-War Struggle 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 3 (KCNA) -- The present worse situation urgently requires the Korean nation to wage a more dynamic struggle against the U.S. and war, Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article says, calling on all the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and abroad to get united as one to check and frustrate the U.S. imperialists' arrogant and criminal moves to invade the DPRK.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and abroad should turn out as one in the struggle to defend peace and security of the country and the sovereign and vital rights of the nation from the U.S. imperialists' aggression and war moves.
 The present reality in which the nation's sovereign and vital rights are gravely threatened by the U.S. imperialist warmongers' frenzy for a war against the DPRK requires the fellow countrymen to turn out in the struggle against the U.S. and war irrespective of ideology, political views, classes and strata. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Flunkeyism and dependence on foreign forces should be rejected in order to safeguard the peace of the country and the security of the nation from the U.S. imperialists' aggression and war moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and abroad should resolutely reject flunkeyism and dependence on outsiders with transparent consciousness and viewpoint of national independence that the issue of keeping peace of the country and the security of the nation can only be solved by the Korean nation itself.
 Stern punishment should be given to the south Korean flunkeyists and traitors including the "Grand National Party" which follow the U.S. imperialists in their criminal hostile policy toward the DPRK, while clamoring for cooperation with outsiders in disregard of the unanimous desire and demand of all the fellow countrymen.
 The Korean nation should support and positively uphold the great patriotic Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy is the patriotic policy which all the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and abroad should follow and uphold altogether.
 The struggle against the U.S. and war is the most urgent task in the history of the nation and the requirement of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when the Korean nation decisively blocks and foils the U.S. imperialists' moves for aggression and war, can it speed up the cause of independent reunification, a long-cherished desire of the fellow countrymen, in the atmosphere of durable peace.

Rodong Sinmun on Single-minded Unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 3 (KCNA) -- Single-minded unity is, indeed, the source of the indestructible spirit and strength of the country not yielding to any difficulties and an invincible weapon we should hold fast to forever in accomplishing the cause of socialism. Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article.
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Single-minded unity serves as a treasured sword which helps consolidate the political and ideological position of the DPRK as firm as a rock in any challenges of the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists and hostile forces are becoming all the more vicious in their ideological and cultural poisoning and psychological warfare in a bid to undermine Korean-style socialism. But no force on earth can break the single-minded unity of the whole army and all the people of the DPRK around the headquarters of the revolution.
 The might of the single-minded unity has been tremendously strengthened thanks to the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il. The transparent outlook on life that one lives for the leader even a moment and that one devotes one's youth and life to upholding the leader all one's life, the transparent revolutionary spirit that one deems death as glory in putting into practice the idea and intention of the leader and fulfilling obligation as soldier, this is the noble ideological and mental world of the Korean army and people on the basis of which they are single-mindedly united. Herein lies the true feature of our society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity serves as a motive force which helps the army and the people create centuries-old feats and miracles in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great spirit that the leader believes in the people and the people absolutely trust and follow the leader is the fundamental source of ceaseless miracles and feats in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The line of economic construction in the era of Songun, the policy on reconstructing and modernizing the national economy, the policy on keeping a great surge in agriculture and other lines and policies of the Workers' Party of Korea have been successfully implemented, so that the national power of the country has been strengthened in every way and the economy put on the track of invigoration and the foundation for fresh leaping progress laid. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity of the whole army and all the people around the leader is, indeed, the most precious wealth of the Korean revolution and a treasured sword of invincible victory more powerful than nuclear weapons.

Halt to Suppression of Human Rights against Chongryon Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 3 (KCNA) -- Representatives of 28 south Korean Buddhist organizations including the Buddhist Human Rights Committee, the Buddhist Peace Solidarity and the Buddhist Women's Society reportedly issued a joint statement titled "Japan should immediately stop suppression of human rights against the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon)" on Nov. 28.
 Recalling that the Japanese authorities sent police to search 7 places including the Tokyo Metropolitan Headquarters of Chongryon, the statement condemned it as an abuse of the human rights of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unpardonable act that the Japanese authorities have addressed themselves to the suppression of Chongryon instead of defending the property of Chongryon and lives of Koreans in Japan and ensuring their human rights, the statement noted, and went on:
 The Japanese authorities have intensified their moves to rig up plots against Chongryon and crackdown on it, availing themselves of the U.S. hostile policy toward the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities should make an apology to the whole Korean nation for their unreasonable crackdown upon Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should be responsible for and repent of the past criminal atrocities against the Koreans.

Sharing Fund for Upkeep of U.S. Forces in S. Korea Rejected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 2 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, an anti-war and peace organization in south Korea, reportedly held a press conference in front of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade in Seoul on Nov. 28 at which it rejected the negotiations on sharing the fund for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea.
 The press conference preceded the sixth negotiations on the conclusion of a special agreement on sharing the fund for the upkeep of the U.S. forces held in Seoul from Nov. 29 to 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the conference denounced the south Korean side, claiming that it is a double or treble burden on its people to cover not only fund for the transfer of the U.S. military bases and their expansion according to the agreement on the transfer of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan and the joint land management program but also the fund for the upkeep of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press release demanded the south Korean "government" foil the U.S. attempt to maintain a lever for unlimited support for the U.S. forces at the forthcoming negotiations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called for halting the farce of offering the fund for the upkeep of the U.S. under the pretext of military support and abrogating the special agreement on sharing the fund for the upkeep of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the press conference its participants waged a struggle to seek an interview with the minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade before entering into a sit-in strike.

People's Actions Staged in Seoul
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 2 (KCNA) -- The second all-people actions were reportedly staged in Seoul on Nov. 29 to check the negotiations for the conclusion of south Korea-U.S. FTA. 
 A meeting was slated to take place in Seoul Railway Station Plaza that day under the sponsorship of the south Korean Agricultural, Stockbreeding and Fisheries Emergency Committee of Measures against FTA but the police completely sealed off the gates to the venue of the event by rushing its 14 companies there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Representatives of peasant organization held a press conference inside the railway station in protest against the police crackdown. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the conference accused the "government" of unilaterally scuttling the meeting by mobilizing the police, utterly indifferent to the pain the peasants would suffer due to the conclusion of the above-said agreement, adding that this has triggered off bitterer resentment among them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 3000 peasants staged meetings and demonstrations in different parts of Seoul. They gathered in the Ulji Intersection after breaking through the police cordon all of a sudden to hold a meeting to rouse all people to actions for checking the conclusion of FTA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the meeting demanded the "government" halt at once the above-mentioned negotiations as FTA is aimed at ruining the life of not only peasants but all other people and leaving everything in this land to the tender mercy of the U.S.
 That evening peasants from various parts of south Korea held a candlelight event in Myongdong in which they vowed to intensify their actions for checking the negotiations.
